This involves analyzing visual features of images, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper addresses the issue of limited network connectivity in developing countries and proposes a solution to reduce memory costs associated with high-memory demanding elements such as images. This is relevant to the field of information retrieval, which deals with efficient storage and retrieval of information. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with multimodal web elements such as text and images and proposes a method to replace high-cost modality with low-cost modality. This falls under the domain of multimedia, which deals with the integration of multiple media types.
